stoneChat (a caveman peeking at modern technology) is a simple LLM Web Chat, adapted for Windows XP & IE6.

To run it, your device needs a PHP 5.2 environment. As for all the remaining network-related problems, let the program handle them.

Download or clone this Project. Run RUN.bat to start the program. You need to edit CONF.ini according to the comments to configure the LLM and other settings -- it is very simple, just follow the comments.

Then visit it in your browser. The default address is:
http://localhost:9999

stoneChat is open-sourced under WTFPL at:
https://github.com/Water-Run/stoneChat
